{"title_page": "Second Hodgman Ministry", "text_new": "The '''Second Hodgman Ministry''' is the current Ministry of the [[Government of Tasmania]], led by [[Will Hodgman]] of the [[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Tasmanian Liberals]]. It was formed on 21 March 2018, after the previous government was re-elected at the [[2018 Tasmanian state election]].<ref name=changes>[https://www.govhouse.tas.gov.au/news/wednesday-21-march-2018  Wednesday 21 March 2018], Governor of Tasmania, 21 March 2018.</ref><ref name=announcement>[https://www.tas.liberal.org.au/news/refreshed-cabinet-deliver-governments-plan  Refreshed Cabinet to deliver Government's Plan], Tasmanian Liberals, 20 March 2018.</ref>\n\nAll members of the ministry, aside from Courtney and Jaensch, previously served in the [[Hodgman Ministry|First Hodgman Ministry]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Portfolio\n! Minister\n! colspan=2 | Party affiliation\n! Term start\n! Term end\n! Term in office\n|-\n|\n* [[Premier of Tasmania|Premier]]\n* Minister for Tourism, Hospitality and Events\n* Minister for Parks\n* Minister for Heritage\n* Minister for Trade\n|| [[Will Hodgman]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|rowspan=9 align=center |{{start date|2018|03|21|df=y}}\n|rowspan=9 align=center |''incumbent''\n|rowspan=9 align=center |{{age in days|2018|03|21}} days\n|-\n|\n* [[Deputy Premier of Tasmania|Deputy Premier]]\n* [[Department of Education (Tasmania)|Minister for Education and Training]]\n* Minister for Infrastructure\n* Minister for Advanced Manufacturing and Defence Industries\n|| [[Jeremy Rockliff]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* [[Treasurer of Tasmania|Treasurer]]\n* Minister for State Growth\n* Minister for Local Government\n|| [[Peter Gutwein]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* [[Department of Health and Human Services (Tasmania)|Minister for Health]]\n* Minister for Police, Fire and Emergency Management\n* Minister for Science and Technology\n|| [[Michael Ferguson (Australian politician)|Michael Ferguson]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* [[Attorney-General of Tasmania|Attorney-General]]\n* Minister for Justice\n* Minister for Corrections\n* Minister for Environment\n* Minister for Arts\n|| [[Elise Archer]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* Minister for Disability Services and Community Development\n* Minister for Aboriginal Affairs\n* Minister for Women\n* Minister for Sport and Recreation\n|| [[Jacquie Petrusma]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* Minister for Resources\n* Minister for Energy\n* Minister for Building and Construction\n* Minister for Veterans' Affairs\n|| [[Guy Barnett (Australian politician)|Guy Barnett]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* Minister for Primary Industries and Water\n* Minister for Racing\n|| [[Sarah Courtney]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small>\n|{{Australian party style|Liberal}}|&nbsp;\n|[[Liberal Party of Australia (Tasmanian Division)|Liberal]]\n|-\n|\n* Minister for Human Services\n* Minister for Housing\n* Minister for Planning\n|| [[Roger Jaensch]] <small>[[Tasmanian House of Assembly|MP]]</small